1. A memory comprising:
a segmented bit line for data access to said memory;
said bit line having segments controlled by a latch repeater.

claim.claim-text:
A memory (20) comprising:
a segmented bit line (25) and/or a segmented word line for data access to said memory (20);
said bit line (25) and/or word line having single-bit and/or single word segments, each segment being controlled by an associated latch repeater (30-A, 30-B, 30-C).

The memory of any one of claims 1 to 4, further comprising:
a plurality of memory arrays (12), said memory arrays (12) being adapted to store data;
wherein access to said memory arrays is controlled by the bit line (25) and/or the word line.
